350 void SymbolTableWriter::writeSymbol(uint32_t name, uint8_t info, uint64_t value, 0
351 uint64_t size, uint8_t other, ----
352 uint32_t shndx, bool Reserved) { ----
353 bool LargeIndex = shndx >= ELF::SHN_LORESERVE && !Reserved; 0
354 ----
355 if (LargeIndex) 0
356 createSymtabShndx(); 0
357 ----
358 if (!ShndxIndexes.empty()) { 0
359 if (LargeIndex) 0
360 ShndxIndexes.push_back(shndx); 0
361 else ----
362 ShndxIndexes.push_back(0); 0
363 } ----
364 ----
365 uint16_t Index = LargeIndex ? uint16_t(ELF::SHN_XINDEX) : shndx; 0
366 ----
367 if (Is64Bit) { 0
368 write(name); // st_name 0
369 write(info); // st_info 0
370 write(other); // st_other 0
371 write(Index); // st_shndx 0
372 write(value); // st_value 0
373 write(size); // st_size 0
374 } else { ----
375 write(name); // st_name 0
376 write(uint32_t(value)); // st_value 0
377 write(uint32_t(size)); // st_size 0
378 write(info); // st_info 0
379 write(other); // st_other 0
380 write(Index); // st_shndx 0
381 } ----
382 ----
383 ++NumWritten; 0
384 } 0

395 // Emit the ELF header. ----
396 void ELFWriter::writeHeader(const MCAssembler &Asm) { 0
397 // ELF Header ----
398 // ---------- ----
399 // ----
400 // Note ----
401 // ---- ----
402 // emitWord method behaves differently for ELF32 and ELF64, writing ----
403 // 4 bytes in the former and 8 in the latter. ----
404 ----
405 W.OS << ELF::ElfMagic; // e_ident[EI_MAG0] to e_ident[EI_MAG3] 0
406 ----
407 W.OS << char(is64Bit() ? ELF::ELFCLASS64 : ELF::ELFCLASS32); // e_ident[EI_CLASS] 0
408 ----
409 // e_ident[EI_DATA] ----
410 W.OS << char(W.Endian == support::little ? ELF::ELFDATA2LSB 0
411 : ELF::ELFDATA2MSB); 0
412 ----
413 W.OS << char(ELF::EV_CURRENT); // e_ident[EI_VERSION] 0
414 // e_ident[EI_OSABI] ----
415 uint8_t OSABI = OWriter.TargetObjectWriter->getOSABI(); 0
416 W.OS << char(OSABI == ELF::ELFOSABI_NONE && OWriter.seenGnuAbi() 0
417 ? int(ELF::ELFOSABI_GNU) ----
418 : OSABI); 0
419 // e_ident[EI_ABIVERSION] ----
420 W.OS << char(OWriter.TargetObjectWriter->getABIVersion()); 0
421 ----
422 W.OS.write_zeros(ELF::EI_NIDENT - ELF::EI_PAD); 0
423 ----
424 W.write(ELF::ET_REL); // e_type 0
425 ----
426 W.write(OWriter.TargetObjectWriter->getEMachine()); // e_machine = target 0
427 ----
428 W.write(ELF::EV_CURRENT); // e_version 0
429 WriteWord(0); // e_entry, no entry point in .o file 0
430 WriteWord(0); // e_phoff, no program header for .o 0
431 WriteWord(0); // e_shoff = sec hdr table off in bytes 0
432 ----
433 // e_flags = whatever the target wants ----
434 W.write(Asm.getELFHeaderEFlags()); 0
435 ----
436 // e_ehsize = ELF header size ----
437 W.write(is64Bit() ? sizeof(ELF::Elf64_Ehdr) 0
438 : sizeof(ELF::Elf32_Ehdr)); ----
439 ----
440 W.write(0); // e_phentsize = prog header entry size 0
441 W.write(0); // e_phnum = # prog header entries = 0 0
442 ----
443 // e_shentsize = Section header entry size ----
444 W.write(is64Bit() ? sizeof(ELF::Elf64_Shdr) 0
445 : sizeof(ELF::Elf32_Shdr)); ----
446 ----
447 // e_shnum = # of section header ents ----
448 W.write(0); 0
449 ----
450 // e_shstrndx = Section # of '.strtab' ----
451 assert(StringTableIndex < ELF::SHN_LORESERVE); 0
452 W.write(StringTableIndex); 0
453 } 0
454 ----
455 uint64_t ELFWriter::SymbolValue(const MCSymbol &Sym, 0
456 const MCAsmLayout &Layout) { ----
457 if (Sym.isCommon()) 0
458 return Sym.getCommonAlignment()->value(); 0
459 ----
460 uint64_t Res; ----
461 if (!Layout.getSymbolOffset(Sym, Res)) 0
462 return 0; 0
463 ----
464 if (Layout.getAssembler().isThumbFunc(&Sym)) 0
465 Res |= 1; 0
466 ----
467 return Res; 0
468 } ----
469 ----
470 static uint8_t mergeTypeForSet(uint8_t origType, uint8_t newType) { 0
471 uint8_t Type = newType; 0
472 ----
473 // Propagation rules: ----
474 // IFUNC > FUNC > OBJECT > NOTYPE ----
475 // TLS_OBJECT > OBJECT > NOTYPE ----
476 // ----
477 // dont let the new type degrade the old type ----
478 switch (origType) { 0
479 default: 0
480 break; 0
481 case ELF::STT_GNU_IFUNC: 0
482 if (Type == ELF::STT_FUNC || Type == ELF::STT_OBJECT || 0
483 Type == ELF::STT_NOTYPE || Type == ELF::STT_TLS) 0
484 Type = ELF::STT_GNU_IFUNC; 0
485 break; 0
486 case ELF::STT_FUNC: 0
487 if (Type == ELF::STT_OBJECT || Type == ELF::STT_NOTYPE || 0
488 Type == ELF::STT_TLS) ----
489 Type = ELF::STT_FUNC; 0
490 break; 0
491 case ELF::STT_OBJECT: 0
492 if (Type == ELF::STT_NOTYPE) 0
493 Type = ELF::STT_OBJECT; 0
494 break; 0
495 case ELF::STT_TLS: 0
496 if (Type == ELF::STT_OBJECT || Type == ELF::STT_NOTYPE || 0
497 Type == ELF::STT_GNU_IFUNC || Type == ELF::STT_FUNC) 0
498 Type = ELF::STT_TLS; 0
499 break; 0
500 } ----
501 ----
502 return Type; 0
503 } ----
504 ----
505 static bool isIFunc(const MCSymbolELF *Symbol) { 0
506 while (Symbol->getType() != ELF::STT_GNU_IFUNC) { 0
507 const MCSymbolRefExpr *Value; ----
508 if (!Symbol->isVariable() || 0
509 !(Value = dyn_cast(Symbol->getVariableValue())) || 0
510 Value->getKind() != MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_None || 0
511 mergeTypeForSet(Symbol->getType(), ELF::STT_GNU_IFUNC) != ELF::STT_GNU_IFUNC) 0
512 return false; 0
513 Symbol = &cast(Value->getSymbol()); 0
514 } ----
515 return true; 0
516 } ----
517 ----
518 void ELFWriter::writeSymbol(SymbolTableWriter &Writer, uint32_t StringIndex, 0
519 ELFSymbolData &MSD, const MCAsmLayout &Layout) { ----
520 const auto &Symbol = cast(*MSD.Symbol); 0
521 const MCSymbolELF *Base = ----
522 cast_or_null(Layout.getBaseSymbol(Symbol)); 0
523 ----
524 // This has to be in sync with when computeSymbolTable uses SHN_ABS or ----
525 // SHN_COMMON. ----
526 bool IsReserved = !Base || Symbol.isCommon(); 0
527 ----
528 // Binding and Type share the same byte as upper and lower nibbles ----
529 uint8_t Binding = Symbol.getBinding(); 0
530 uint8_t Type = Symbol.getType(); 0
531 if (isIFunc(&Symbol)) 0
532 Type = ELF::STT_GNU_IFUNC; 0
533 if (Base) { 0
534 Type = mergeTypeForSet(Type, Base->getType()); 0
535 } ----
536 uint8_t Info = (Binding << 4) | Type; 0
537 ----
538 // Other and Visibility share the same byte with Visibility using the lower ----
539 // 2 bits ----
540 uint8_t Visibility = Symbol.getVisibility(); 0
541 uint8_t Other = Symbol.getOther() | Visibility; 0
542 ----
543 uint64_t Value = SymbolValue(*MSD.Symbol, Layout); 0
544 uint64_t Size = 0; 0
545 ----
546 const MCExpr *ESize = MSD.Symbol->getSize(); 0
547 if (!ESize && Base) { 0
548 // For expressions like .set y, x+1, if y's size is unset, inherit from x. ----
549 ESize = Base->getSize(); 0
550 ----
551 // For `.size x, 2; y = x; .size y, 1; z = y; z1 = z; .symver y, y@v1`, z, ----
552 // z1, and y@v1's st_size equals y's. However, `Base` is `x` which will give ----
553 // us 2. Follow the MCSymbolRefExpr assignment chain, which covers most ----
554 // needs. MCBinaryExpr is not handled. ----
555 const MCSymbolELF *Sym = &Symbol; 0
556 while (Sym->isVariable()) { 0
557 if (auto *Expr = 0
558 dyn_cast(Sym->getVariableValue(false))) { 0
559 Sym = cast(&Expr->getSymbol()); 0
560 if (!Sym->getSize()) 0
561 continue; 0
562 ESize = Sym->getSize(); 0
563 } ----
564 break; 0
565 } ----
566 } ----
567 ----
568 if (ESize) { 0
569 int64_t Res; ----
570 if (!ESize->evaluateKnownAbsolute(Res, Layout)) 0
571 report_fatal_error("Size expression must be absolute."); 0
572 Size = Res; 0
573 } ----
574 ----
575 // Write out the symbol table entry ----
576 Writer.writeSymbol(StringIndex, Info, Value, Size, Other, MSD.SectionIndex, 0
577 IsReserved); ----
578 } 0
579 ----
580 bool ELFWriter::isInSymtab(const MCAsmLayout &Layout, const MCSymbolELF &Symbol, 0
581 bool Used, bool Renamed) { ----
582 if (Symbol.isVariable()) { 0
583 const MCExpr *Expr = Symbol.getVariableValue(); 0
584 // Target Expressions that are always inlined do not appear in the symtab ----
585 if (const auto *T = dyn_cast(Expr)) 0
586 if (T->inlineAssignedExpr()) 0
587 return false; 0
588 if (const MCSymbolRefExpr *Ref = dyn_cast(Expr)) { 0
589 if (Ref->getKind() == MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_WEAKREF) 0
590 return false; 0
591 } ----
592 } ----
593 ----
594 if (Used) 0
595 return true; 0
596 ----
597 if (Renamed) 0
598 return false; 0
599 ----
600 if (Symbol.isVariable() && Symbol.isUndefined()) { 0
601 // FIXME: this is here just to diagnose the case of a var = commmon_sym. ----
602 Layout.getBaseSymbol(Symbol); 0
603 return false; 0
604 } ----
605 ----
606 if (Symbol.isTemporary()) 0
607 return false; 0
608 ----
609 if (Symbol.getType() == ELF::STT_SECTION) 0
610 return false; 0
611 ----
612 return true; 0
613 } ----
614 ----
615 void ELFWriter::createMemtagRelocs(MCAssembler &Asm) { 0
616 MCSectionELF *MemtagRelocs = nullptr; 0
617 for (const MCSymbol &Sym : Asm.symbols()) { 0
618 const auto &SymE = cast(Sym); 0
619 if (!SymE.isMemtag()) 0
620 continue; 0
621 if (MemtagRelocs == nullptr) { 0
622 MemtagRelocs = OWriter.TargetObjectWriter->getMemtagRelocsSection(Asm.getContext()); 0
623 if (MemtagRelocs == nullptr) 0
624 report_fatal_error("Tagged globals are not available on this architecture."); 0
625 Asm.registerSection(*MemtagRelocs); 0
626 } ----
627 ELFRelocationEntry Rec(0, &SymE, ELF::R_AARCH64_NONE, 0, nullptr, 0); 0
628 OWriter.Relocations[MemtagRelocs].push_back(Rec); 0
629 } ----
630 } 0
631 ----
632 void ELFWriter::computeSymbolTable( 0
633 MCAssembler &Asm, const MCAsmLayout &Layout, ----
634 const SectionIndexMapTy &SectionIndexMap, const RevGroupMapTy &RevGroupMap, ----
635 SectionOffsetsTy &SectionOffsets) { ----
636 MCContext &Ctx = Asm.getContext(); 0
637 SymbolTableWriter Writer(*this, is64Bit()); 0
638 ----
639 // Symbol table ----
640 unsigned EntrySize = is64Bit() ? ELF::SYMENTRY_SIZE64 : ELF::SYMENTRY_SIZE32; 0
641 MCSectionELF *SymtabSection = ----
642 Ctx.getELFSection(".symtab", ELF::SHT_SYMTAB, 0, EntrySize); 0
643 SymtabSection->setAlignment(is64Bit() ? Align(8) : Align(4)); 0
644 SymbolTableIndex = addToSectionTable(SymtabSection); 0
645 ----
646 uint64_t SecStart = align(SymtabSection->getAlign()); 0
647 ----
648 // The first entry is the undefined symbol entry. ----
649 Writer.writeSymbol(0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, false); 0
650 ----
651 std::vector LocalSymbolData; 0
652 std::vector ExternalSymbolData; 0
653 MutableArrayRef> FileNames = ----
654 Asm.getFileNames(); 0
655 for (const std::pair &F : FileNames) 0
656 StrTabBuilder.add(F.first); 0
657 ----
658 // Add the data for the symbols. ----
659 bool HasLargeSectionIndex = false; 0
660 for (auto It : llvm::enumerate(Asm.symbols())) { 0
661 const auto &Symbol = cast(It.value()); 0
662 bool Used = Symbol.isUsedInReloc(); 0
663 bool WeakrefUsed = Symbol.isWeakrefUsedInReloc(); 0
664 bool isSignature = Symbol.isSignature(); 0
665 ----
666 if (!isInSymtab(Layout, Symbol, Used || WeakrefUsed || isSignature, 0
667 OWriter.Renames.count(&Symbol))) 0
668 continue; 0
669 ----
670 if (Symbol.isTemporary() && Symbol.isUndefined()) { 0
671 Ctx.reportError(SMLoc(), "Undefined temporary symbol " + Symbol.getName()); 0
672 continue; 0
673 } ----
674 ----
675 ELFSymbolData MSD; 0
676 MSD.Symbol = cast(&Symbol); 0
677 MSD.Order = It.index(); 0
678 ----
679 bool Local = Symbol.getBinding() == ELF::STB_LOCAL; 0
680 assert(Local || !Symbol.isTemporary()); 0
681 ----
682 if (Symbol.isAbsolute()) { 0
683 MSD.SectionIndex = ELF::SHN_ABS; 0
684 } else if (Symbol.isCommon()) { 0
685 if (Symbol.isTargetCommon()) { 0
686 MSD.SectionIndex = Symbol.getIndex(); 0
687 } else { ----
688 assert(!Local); 0
689 MSD.SectionIndex = ELF::SHN_COMMON; 0
690 } ----
691 } else if (Symbol.isUndefined()) { 0
692 if (isSignature && !Used) { 0
693 MSD.SectionIndex = RevGroupMap.lookup(&Symbol); 0
694 if (MSD.SectionIndex >= ELF::SHN_LORESERVE) 0
695 HasLargeSectionIndex = true; 0
696 } else { ----
697 MSD.SectionIndex = ELF::SHN_UNDEF; 0
698 } ----
699 } else { ----
700 const MCSectionELF &Section = ----
701 static_cast(Symbol.getSection()); 0
702 ----
703 // We may end up with a situation when section symbol is technically ----
704 // defined, but should not be. That happens because we explicitly ----
705 // pre-create few .debug_* sections to have accessors. ----
706 // And if these sections were not really defined in the code, but were ----
707 // referenced, we simply error out. ----
708 if (!Section.isRegistered()) { 0
709 assert(static_cast(Symbol).getType() == 0
710 ELF::STT_SECTION); ----
711 Ctx.reportError(SMLoc(), 0
712 "Undefined section reference: " + Symbol.getName()); 0
713 continue; 0
714 } ----
715 ----
716 if (Mode == NonDwoOnly && isDwoSection(Section)) 0
717 continue; 0
718 MSD.SectionIndex = SectionIndexMap.lookup(&Section); 0
719 assert(MSD.SectionIndex && "Invalid section index!"); 0
720 if (MSD.SectionIndex >= ELF::SHN_LORESERVE) 0
721 HasLargeSectionIndex = true; 0
722 } ----
723 ----
724 StringRef Name = Symbol.getName(); 0
725 ----
726 // Sections have their own string table ----
727 if (Symbol.getType() != ELF::STT_SECTION) { 0
728 MSD.Name = Name; 0
729 StrTabBuilder.add(Name); 0
730 } ----
731 ----
732 if (Local) 0
733 LocalSymbolData.push_back(MSD); 0
734 else ----
735 ExternalSymbolData.push_back(MSD); 0
736 } ----
737 ----
738 // This holds the .symtab_shndx section index. ----
739 unsigned SymtabShndxSectionIndex = 0; 0
740 ----
741 if (HasLargeSectionIndex) { 0
742 MCSectionELF *SymtabShndxSection = ----
743 Ctx.getELFSection(".symtab_shndx", ELF::SHT_SYMTAB_SHNDX, 0, 4); 0
744 SymtabShndxSectionIndex = addToSectionTable(SymtabShndxSection); 0
745 SymtabShndxSection->setAlignment(Align(4)); 0
746 } ----
747 ----
748 StrTabBuilder.finalize(); 0
749 ----
750 // Make the first STT_FILE precede previous local symbols. ----
751 unsigned Index = 1; 0
752 auto FileNameIt = FileNames.begin(); 0
753 if (!FileNames.empty()) 0
754 FileNames[0].second = 0; 0
755 ----
756 for (ELFSymbolData &MSD : LocalSymbolData) { 0
757 // Emit STT_FILE symbols before their associated local symbols. ----
758 for (; FileNameIt != FileNames.end() && FileNameIt->second <= MSD.Order; 0
759 ++FileNameIt) { ----
760 Writer.writeSymbol(StrTabBuilder.getOffset(FileNameIt->first), 0
761 ELF::STT_FILE | ELF::STB_LOCAL, 0, 0, ELF::STV_DEFAULT, ----
762 ELF::SHN_ABS, true); ----
763 ++Index; 0
764 } ----
765 ----
766 unsigned StringIndex = MSD.Symbol->getType() == ELF::STT_SECTION 0
767 ? 0 ----
768 : StrTabBuilder.getOffset(MSD.Name); 0
769 MSD.Symbol->setIndex(Index++); 0
770 writeSymbol(Writer, StringIndex, MSD, Layout); 0
771 } ----
772 for (; FileNameIt != FileNames.end(); ++FileNameIt) { 0
773 Writer.writeSymbol(StrTabBuilder.getOffset(FileNameIt->first), 0
774 ELF::STT_FILE | ELF::STB_LOCAL, 0, 0, ELF::STV_DEFAULT, ----
775 ELF::SHN_ABS, true); ----
776 ++Index; 0
777 } ----
778 ----
779 // Write the symbol table entries. ----
780 LastLocalSymbolIndex = Index; 0
781 ----
782 for (ELFSymbolData &MSD : ExternalSymbolData) { 0
783 unsigned StringIndex = StrTabBuilder.getOffset(MSD.Name); 0
784 MSD.Symbol->setIndex(Index++); 0
785 writeSymbol(Writer, StringIndex, MSD, Layout); 0
786 assert(MSD.Symbol->getBinding() != ELF::STB_LOCAL); 0
787 } ----
788 ----
789 uint64_t SecEnd = W.OS.tell(); 0
790 SectionOffsets[SymtabSection] = std::make_pair(SecStart, SecEnd); 0
791 ----
792 ArrayRef ShndxIndexes = Writer.getShndxIndexes(); 0
793 if (ShndxIndexes.empty()) { 0
794 assert(SymtabShndxSectionIndex == 0); 0
795 return; 0
796 } ----
797 assert(SymtabShndxSectionIndex != 0); 0
798 ----
799 SecStart = W.OS.tell(); 0
800 const MCSectionELF *SymtabShndxSection = ----
801 SectionTable[SymtabShndxSectionIndex - 1]; 0
802 for (uint32_t Index : ShndxIndexes) 0
803 write(Index); 0
804 SecEnd = W.OS.tell(); 0
805 SectionOffsets[SymtabShndxSection] = std::make_pair(SecStart, SecEnd); 0
806 } 0
807 ----
808 void ELFWriter::writeAddrsigSection() { 0
809 for (const MCSymbol *Sym : OWriter.AddrsigSyms) 0
810 if (Sym->getIndex() != 0) 0
811 encodeULEB128(Sym->getIndex(), W.OS); 0
812 } 0
813 ----
814 MCSectionELF *ELFWriter::createRelocationSection(MCContext &Ctx, 0
815 const MCSectionELF &Sec) { ----
816 if (OWriter.Relocations[&Sec].empty()) 0
817 return nullptr; 0
818 ----
819 const StringRef SectionName = Sec.getName(); 0
820 bool Rela = usesRela(Sec); 0
821 std::string RelaSectionName = Rela ? ".rela" : ".rel"; 0
822 RelaSectionName += SectionName; 0
823 ----
824 unsigned EntrySize; ----
825 if (Rela) 0
826 EntrySize = is64Bit() ? sizeof(ELF::Elf64_Rela) : sizeof(ELF::Elf32_Rela); 0
827 else ----
828 EntrySize = is64Bit() ? sizeof(ELF::Elf64_Rel) : sizeof(ELF::Elf32_Rel); 0
829 ----
830 unsigned Flags = ELF::SHF_INFO_LINK; 0
831 if (Sec.getFlags() & ELF::SHF_GROUP) 0
832 Flags = ELF::SHF_GROUP; 0
833 ----
834 MCSectionELF *RelaSection = Ctx.createELFRelSection( 0
835 RelaSectionName, Rela ? ELF::SHT_RELA : ELF::SHT_REL, Flags, EntrySize, ----
836 Sec.getGroup(), &Sec); ----
837 RelaSection->setAlignment(is64Bit() ? Align(8) : Align(4)); 0
838 return RelaSection; 0
839 } 0
840 ----
841 // Include the debug info compression header. ----
842 bool ELFWriter::maybeWriteCompression( 0
843 uint32_t ChType, uint64_t Size, ----
844 SmallVectorImpl &CompressedContents, Align Alignment) { ----
845 uint64_t HdrSize = ----
846 is64Bit() ? sizeof(ELF::Elf32_Chdr) : sizeof(ELF::Elf64_Chdr); 0
847 if (Size <= HdrSize + CompressedContents.size()) 0
848 return false; 0
849 // Platform specific header is followed by compressed data. ----
850 if (is64Bit()) { 0
851 // Write Elf64_Chdr header. ----
852 write(static_cast(ChType)); 0
853 write(static_cast(0)); // ch_reserved field. 0
854 write(static_cast(Size)); 0
855 write(static_cast(Alignment.value())); 0
856 } else { ----
857 // Write Elf32_Chdr header otherwise. ----
858 write(static_cast(ChType)); 0
859 write(static_cast(Size)); 0
860 write(static_cast(Alignment.value())); 0
861 } ----
862 return true; 0
863 } ----
864 ----
865 void ELFWriter::writeSectionData(const MCAssembler &Asm, MCSection &Sec, 0
866 const MCAsmLayout &Layout) { ----
867 MCSectionELF &Section = static_cast(Sec); 0
868 StringRef SectionName = Section.getName(); 0
869 ----
870 auto &MC = Asm.getContext(); 0
871 const auto &MAI = MC.getAsmInfo(); 0
872 ----
873 const DebugCompressionType CompressionType = MAI->compressDebugSections(); 0
874 if (CompressionType == DebugCompressionType::None || 0
875 !SectionName.startswith(".debug_")) { 0
876 Asm.writeSectionData(W.OS, &Section, Layout); 0
877 return; 0
878 } ----
879 ----
880 SmallVector UncompressedData; 0
881 raw_svector_ostream VecOS(UncompressedData); 0
882 Asm.writeSectionData(VecOS, &Section, Layout); 0
883 ArrayRef Uncompressed = ----
884 ArrayRef(reinterpret_cast(UncompressedData.data()), 0
885 UncompressedData.size()); 0
886 ----
887 SmallVector Compressed; 0
888 uint32_t ChType; ----
889 switch (CompressionType) { 0
890 case DebugCompressionType::None: 0
891 llvm_unreachable("has been handled"); 0
892 case DebugCompressionType::Zlib: 0
893 ChType = ELF::ELFCOMPRESS_ZLIB; 0
894 break; 0
895 case DebugCompressionType::Zstd: 0
896 ChType = ELF::ELFCOMPRESS_ZSTD; 0
897 break; 0
898 } ----
899 compression::compress(compression::Params(CompressionType), Uncompressed, 0
900 Compressed); ----
901 if (!maybeWriteCompression(ChType, UncompressedData.size(), Compressed, 0
902 Sec.getAlign())) { ----
903 W.OS << UncompressedData; 0
904 return; 0
905 } ----
906 ----
907 Section.setFlags(Section.getFlags() | ELF::SHF_COMPRESSED); 0
908 // Alignment field should reflect the requirements of ----
909 // the compressed section header. ----
910 Section.setAlignment(is64Bit() ? Align(8) : Align(4)); 0
911 W.OS << toStringRef(Compressed); 0
912 } 0
913 ----
914 void ELFWriter::WriteSecHdrEntry(uint32_t Name, uint32_t Type, uint64_t Flags, 0
915 uint64_t Address, uint64_t Offset, ----
916 uint64_t Size, uint32_t Link, uint32_t Info, ----
917 MaybeAlign Alignment, uint64_t EntrySize) { ----
918 W.write(Name); // sh_name: index into string table 0
919 W.write(Type); // sh_type 0
920 WriteWord(Flags); // sh_flags 0
921 WriteWord(Address); // sh_addr 0
922 WriteWord(Offset); // sh_offset 0
923 WriteWord(Size); // sh_size 0
924 W.write(Link); // sh_link 0
925 W.write(Info); // sh_info 0
926 WriteWord(Alignment ? Alignment->value() : 0); // sh_addralign 0
927 WriteWord(EntrySize); // sh_entsize 0
928 } 0
929 ----
930 void ELFWriter::writeRelocations(const MCAssembler &Asm, 0
931 const MCSectionELF &Sec) { ----
932 std::vector &Relocs = OWriter.Relocations[&Sec]; 0
933 ----
934 // We record relocations by pushing to the end of a vector. Reverse the vector ----
935 // to get the relocations in the order they were created. ----
936 // In most cases that is not important, but it can be for special sections ----
937 // (.eh_frame) or specific relocations (TLS optimizations on SystemZ). ----
938 std::reverse(Relocs.begin(), Relocs.end()); 0
939 ----
940 // Sort the relocation entries. MIPS needs this. ----
941 OWriter.TargetObjectWriter->sortRelocs(Asm, Relocs); 0
942 ----
943 const bool Rela = usesRela(Sec); 0
944 for (unsigned i = 0, e = Relocs.size(); i != e; ++i) { 0
945 const ELFRelocationEntry &Entry = Relocs[e - i - 1]; 0
946 unsigned Index = Entry.Symbol ? Entry.Symbol->getIndex() : 0; 0
947 ----
948 if (is64Bit()) { 0
949 write(Entry.Offset); 0
950 if (OWriter.TargetObjectWriter->getEMachine() == ELF::EM_MIPS) { 0
951 write(uint32_t(Index)); 0
952 ----
953 write(OWriter.TargetObjectWriter->getRSsym(Entry.Type)); 0
954 write(OWriter.TargetObjectWriter->getRType3(Entry.Type)); 0
955 write(OWriter.TargetObjectWriter->getRType2(Entry.Type)); 0
956 write(OWriter.TargetObjectWriter->getRType(Entry.Type)); 0
957 } else { ----
958 struct ELF::Elf64_Rela ERE64; ----
959 ERE64.setSymbolAndType(Index, Entry.Type); 0
960 write(ERE64.r_info); 0
961 } ----
962 if (Rela) 0
963 write(Entry.Addend); 0
964 } else { ----
965 write(uint32_t(Entry.Offset)); 0
966 ----
967 struct ELF::Elf32_Rela ERE32; ----
968 ERE32.setSymbolAndType(Index, Entry.Type); 0
969 write(ERE32.r_info); 0
970 ----
971 if (Rela) 0
972 write(uint32_t(Entry.Addend)); 0
973 ----
974 if (OWriter.TargetObjectWriter->getEMachine() == ELF::EM_MIPS) { 0
975 if (uint32_t RType = 0
976 OWriter.TargetObjectWriter->getRType2(Entry.Type)) { 0
977 write(uint32_t(Entry.Offset)); 0
978 ----
979 ERE32.setSymbolAndType(0, RType); 0
980 write(ERE32.r_info); 0
981 write(uint32_t(0)); 0
982 } ----
983 if (uint32_t RType = 0
984 OWriter.TargetObjectWriter->getRType3(Entry.Type)) { 0
985 write(uint32_t(Entry.Offset)); 0
986 ----
987 ERE32.setSymbolAndType(0, RType); 0
988 write(ERE32.r_info); 0
989 write(uint32_t(0)); 0
990 } ----
991 } ----
992 } ----
993 } ----
994 } 0
995 ----
996 void ELFWriter::writeSection(const SectionIndexMapTy &SectionIndexMap, 0
997 uint32_t GroupSymbolIndex, uint64_t Offset, ----
998 uint64_t Size, const MCSectionELF &Section) { ----
999 uint64_t sh_link = 0; 0
1000 uint64_t sh_info = 0; 0
1001 ----
1002 switch(Section.getType()) { 0
1003 default: 0
1004 // Nothing to do. ----
1005 break; 0
1006 ----
1007 case ELF::SHT_DYNAMIC: 0
1008 llvm_unreachable("SHT_DYNAMIC in a relocatable object"); 0
1009 ----
1010 case ELF::SHT_REL: 0
1011 case ELF::SHT_RELA: { ----
1012 sh_link = SymbolTableIndex; 0
1013 assert(sh_link && ".symtab not found"); 0
1014 const MCSection *InfoSection = Section.getLinkedToSection(); 0
1015 sh_info = SectionIndexMap.lookup(cast(InfoSection)); 0
1016 break; 0
1017 } ----
1018 ----
1019 case ELF::SHT_SYMTAB: 0
1020 sh_link = StringTableIndex; 0
1021 sh_info = LastLocalSymbolIndex; 0
1022 break; 0
1023 ----
1024 case ELF::SHT_SYMTAB_SHNDX: 0
1025 case ELF::SHT_LLVM_CALL_GRAPH_PROFILE: ----
1026 case ELF::SHT_LLVM_ADDRSIG: ----
1027 sh_link = SymbolTableIndex; 0
1028 break; 0
1029 ----
1030 case ELF::SHT_GROUP: 0
1031 sh_link = SymbolTableIndex; 0
1032 sh_info = GroupSymbolIndex; 0
1033 break; 0
1034 } ----
1035 ----
1036 if (Section.getFlags() & ELF::SHF_LINK_ORDER) { 0
1037 // If the value in the associated metadata is not a definition, Sym will be ----
1038 // undefined. Represent this with sh_link=0. ----
1039 const MCSymbol *Sym = Section.getLinkedToSymbol(); 0
1040 if (Sym && Sym->isInSection()) { 0
1041 const MCSectionELF *Sec = cast(&Sym->getSection()); 0
1042 sh_link = SectionIndexMap.lookup(Sec); 0
1043 } ----
1044 } ----
1045 ----
1046 WriteSecHdrEntry(StrTabBuilder.getOffset(Section.getName()), 0
1047 Section.getType(), Section.getFlags(), 0, Offset, Size, 0
1048 sh_link, sh_info, Section.getAlign(), ----
1049 Section.getEntrySize()); 0
1050 } 0
1051 ----
1052 void ELFWriter::writeSectionHeader( 0
1053 const MCAsmLayout &Layout, const SectionIndexMapTy &SectionIndexMap, ----
1054 const SectionOffsetsTy &SectionOffsets) { ----
1055 const unsigned NumSections = SectionTable.size(); 0
1056 ----
1057 // Null section first. ----
1058 uint64_t FirstSectionSize = 0
1059 (NumSections + 1) >= ELF::SHN_LORESERVE ? NumSections + 1 : 0; 0
1060 WriteSecHdrEntry(0, 0, 0, 0, 0, FirstSectionSize, 0, 0, std::nullopt, 0); 0
1061 ----
1062 for (const MCSectionELF *Section : SectionTable) { 0
1063 uint32_t GroupSymbolIndex; ----
1064 unsigned Type = Section->getType(); 0
1065 if (Type != ELF::SHT_GROUP) 0
1066 GroupSymbolIndex = 0; 0
1067 else ----
1068 GroupSymbolIndex = Section->getGroup()->getIndex(); 0
1069 ----
1070 const std::pair &Offsets = ----
1071 SectionOffsets.find(Section)->second; 0
1072 uint64_t Size; ----
1073 if (Type == ELF::SHT_NOBITS) 0
1074 Size = Layout.getSectionAddressSize(Section); 0
1075 else ----
1076 Size = Offsets.second - Offsets.first; 0
1077 ----
1078 writeSection(SectionIndexMap, GroupSymbolIndex, Offsets.first, Size, 0
1079 *Section); ----
1080 } ----
1081 } 0
1082 ----
1083 uint64_t ELFWriter::writeObject(MCAssembler &Asm, const MCAsmLayout &Layout) { 0
1084 uint64_t StartOffset = W.OS.tell(); 0
1085 ----
1086 MCContext &Ctx = Asm.getContext(); 0
1087 MCSectionELF *StrtabSection = ----
1088 Ctx.getELFSection(".strtab", ELF::SHT_STRTAB, 0); 0
1089 StringTableIndex = addToSectionTable(StrtabSection); 0
1090 ----
1091 createMemtagRelocs(Asm); 0
1092 ----
1093 RevGroupMapTy RevGroupMap; 0
1094 SectionIndexMapTy SectionIndexMap; 0
1095 ----
1096 std::map> GroupMembers; 0
1097 ----
1098 // Write out the ELF header ... ----
1099 writeHeader(Asm); 0
1100 ----
1101 // ... then the sections ... ----
1102 SectionOffsetsTy SectionOffsets; 0
1103 std::vector Groups; 0
1104 std::vector Relocations; 0
1105 for (MCSection &Sec : Asm) { 0
1106 MCSectionELF &Section = static_cast(Sec); 0
1107 if (Mode == NonDwoOnly && isDwoSection(Section)) 0
1108 continue; 0
1109 if (Mode == DwoOnly && !isDwoSection(Section)) 0
1110 continue; 0
1111 ----
1112 // Remember the offset into the file for this section. ----
1113 const uint64_t SecStart = align(Section.getAlign()); 0
1114 ----
1115 const MCSymbolELF *SignatureSymbol = Section.getGroup(); 0
1116 writeSectionData(Asm, Section, Layout); 0
1117 ----
1118 uint64_t SecEnd = W.OS.tell(); 0
1119 SectionOffsets[&Section] = std::make_pair(SecStart, SecEnd); 0
1120 ----
1121 MCSectionELF *RelSection = createRelocationSection(Ctx, Section); 0
1122 ----
1123 if (SignatureSymbol) { 0
1124 unsigned &GroupIdx = RevGroupMap[SignatureSymbol]; 0
1125 if (!GroupIdx) { 0
1126 MCSectionELF *Group = ----
1127 Ctx.createELFGroupSection(SignatureSymbol, Section.isComdat()); 0
1128 GroupIdx = addToSectionTable(Group); 0
1129 Group->setAlignment(Align(4)); 0
1130 Groups.push_back(Group); 0
1131 } ----
1132 std::vector &Members = ----
1133 GroupMembers[SignatureSymbol]; 0
1134 Members.push_back(&Section); 0
1135 if (RelSection) 0
1136 Members.push_back(RelSection); 0
1137 } ----
1138 ----
1139 SectionIndexMap[&Section] = addToSectionTable(&Section); 0
1140 if (RelSection) { 0
1141 SectionIndexMap[RelSection] = addToSectionTable(RelSection); 0
1142 Relocations.push_back(RelSection); 0
1143 } ----
1144 ----
1145 OWriter.TargetObjectWriter->addTargetSectionFlags(Ctx, Section); 0
1146 } ----
1147 ----
1148 for (MCSectionELF *Group : Groups) { 0
1149 // Remember the offset into the file for this section. ----
1150 const uint64_t SecStart = align(Group->getAlign()); 0
1151 ----
1152 const MCSymbol *SignatureSymbol = Group->getGroup(); 0
1153 assert(SignatureSymbol); 0
1154 write(uint32_t(Group->isComdat() ? unsigned(ELF::GRP_COMDAT) : 0)); 0
1155 for (const MCSectionELF *Member : GroupMembers[SignatureSymbol]) { 0
1156 uint32_t SecIndex = SectionIndexMap.lookup(Member); 0
1157 write(SecIndex); 0
1158 } ----
1159 ----
1160 uint64_t SecEnd = W.OS.tell(); 0
1161 SectionOffsets[Group] = std::make_pair(SecStart, SecEnd); 0
1162 } ----
1163 ----
1164 if (Mode == DwoOnly) { 0
1165 // dwo files don't have symbol tables or relocations, but they do have ----
1166 // string tables. ----
1167 StrTabBuilder.finalize(); 0
1168 } else { ----
1169 MCSectionELF *AddrsigSection; ----
1170 if (OWriter.EmitAddrsigSection) { 0
1171 AddrsigSection = Ctx.getELFSection(".llvm_addrsig", ELF::SHT_LLVM_ADDRSIG, 0
1172 ELF::SHF_EXCLUDE); ----
1173 addToSectionTable(AddrsigSection); 0
1174 } ----
1175 ----
1176 // Compute symbol table information. ----
1177 computeSymbolTable(Asm, Layout, SectionIndexMap, RevGroupMap, 0
1178 SectionOffsets); ----
1179 ----
1180 for (MCSectionELF *RelSection : Relocations) { 0
1181 // Remember the offset into the file for this section. ----
1182 const uint64_t SecStart = align(RelSection->getAlign()); 0
1183 ----
1184 writeRelocations(Asm, 0
1185 cast(*RelSection->getLinkedToSection())); 0
1186 ----
1187 uint64_t SecEnd = W.OS.tell(); 0
1188 SectionOffsets[RelSection] = std::make_pair(SecStart, SecEnd); 0
1189 } ----
1190 ----
1191 if (OWriter.EmitAddrsigSection) { 0
1192 uint64_t SecStart = W.OS.tell(); 0
1193 writeAddrsigSection(); 0
1194 uint64_t SecEnd = W.OS.tell(); 0
1195 SectionOffsets[AddrsigSection] = std::make_pair(SecStart, SecEnd); 0
1196 } ----
1197 } ----
1198 ----
1199 { ----
1200 uint64_t SecStart = W.OS.tell(); 0
1201 StrTabBuilder.write(W.OS); 0
1202 SectionOffsets[StrtabSection] = std::make_pair(SecStart, W.OS.tell()); 0
1203 } ----
1204 ----
1205 const uint64_t SectionHeaderOffset = align(is64Bit() ? Align(8) : Align(4)); 0
1206 ----
1207 // ... then the section header table ... ----
1208 writeSectionHeader(Layout, SectionIndexMap, SectionOffsets); 0
1209 ----
1210 uint16_t NumSections = support::endian::byte_swap( 0
1211 (SectionTable.size() + 1 >= ELF::SHN_LORESERVE) ? (uint16_t)ELF::SHN_UNDEF 0
1212 : SectionTable.size() + 1, 0
1213 W.Endian); 0
1214 unsigned NumSectionsOffset; ----
1215 ----
1216 auto &Stream = static_cast(W.OS); 0
1217 if (is64Bit()) { 0
1218 uint64_t Val = ----
1219 support::endian::byte_swap(SectionHeaderOffset, W.Endian); 0
1220 Stream.pwrite(reinterpret_cast(&Val), sizeof(Val), 0
1221 offsetof(ELF::Elf64_Ehdr, e_shoff)); ----
1222 NumSectionsOffset = offsetof(ELF::Elf64_Ehdr, e_shnum); 0
1223 } else { ----
1224 uint32_t Val = ----
1225 support::endian::byte_swap(SectionHeaderOffset, W.Endian); 0
1226 Stream.pwrite(reinterpret_cast(&Val), sizeof(Val), 0
1227 offsetof(ELF::Elf32_Ehdr, e_shoff)); ----
1228 NumSectionsOffset = offsetof(ELF::Elf32_Ehdr, e_shnum); 0
1229 } ----
1230 Stream.pwrite(reinterpret_cast(&NumSections), sizeof(NumSections), 0
1231 NumSectionsOffset); ----
1232 ----
1233 return W.OS.tell() - StartOffset; 0
1234 } 0
1235 ----
1236 bool ELFObjectWriter::hasRelocationAddend() const { 0
1237 return TargetObjectWriter->hasRelocationAddend(); 0
1238 } ----
1239 ----
1240 void ELFObjectWriter::executePostLayoutBinding(MCAssembler &Asm, 0
1241 const MCAsmLayout &Layout) { ----
1242 // The presence of symbol versions causes undefined symbols and ----
1243 // versions declared with @@@ to be renamed. ----
1244 for (const MCAssembler::Symver &S : Asm.Symvers) { 0
1245 StringRef AliasName = S.Name; 0
1246 const auto &Symbol = cast(*S.Sym); 0
1247 size_t Pos = AliasName.find('@'); 0
1248 assert(Pos != StringRef::npos); 0
1249 ----
1250 StringRef Prefix = AliasName.substr(0, Pos); 0
1251 StringRef Rest = AliasName.substr(Pos); 0
1252 StringRef Tail = Rest; 0
1253 if (Rest.startswith("@@@")) 0
1254 Tail = Rest.substr(Symbol.isUndefined() ? 2 : 1); 0
1255 ----
1256 auto *Alias = ----
1257 cast(Asm.getContext().getOrCreateSymbol(Prefix + Tail)); 0
1258 Asm.registerSymbol(*Alias); 0
1259 const MCExpr *Value = MCSymbolRefExpr::create(&Symbol, Asm.getContext()); 0
1260 Alias->setVariableValue(Value); 0
1261 ----
1262 // Aliases defined with .symvar copy the binding from the symbol they alias. ----
1263 // This is the first place we are able to copy this information. ----
1264 Alias->setBinding(Symbol.getBinding()); 0
1265 Alias->setVisibility(Symbol.getVisibility()); 0
1266 Alias->setOther(Symbol.getOther()); 0
1267 ----
1268 if (!Symbol.isUndefined() && S.KeepOriginalSym) 0
1269 continue; 0
1270 ----
1271 if (Symbol.isUndefined() && Rest.startswith("@@") && 0
1272 !Rest.startswith("@@@")) { 0
1273 Asm.getContext().reportError(S.Loc, "default version symbol " + 0
1274 AliasName + " must be defined"); 0
1275 continue; 0
1276 } ----
1277 ----
1278 if (Renames.count(&Symbol) && Renames[&Symbol] != Alias) { 0
1279 Asm.getContext().reportError(S.Loc, Twine("multiple versions for ") + 0
1280 Symbol.getName()); 0
1281 continue; 0
1282 } ----
1283 ----
1284 Renames.insert(std::make_pair(&Symbol, Alias)); 0
1285 } ----
1286 ----
1287 for (const MCSymbol *&Sym : AddrsigSyms) { 0
1288 if (const MCSymbol *R = Renames.lookup(cast(Sym))) 0
1289 Sym = R; 0
1290 if (Sym->isInSection() && Sym->getName().startswith(".L")) 0
1291 Sym = Sym->getSection().getBeginSymbol(); 0
1292 Sym->setUsedInReloc(); 0
1293 } ----
1294 } 0
1295 ----
1296 // It is always valid to create a relocation with a symbol. It is preferable ----
1297 // to use a relocation with a section if that is possible. Using the section ----
1298 // allows us to omit some local symbols from the symbol table. ----
1299 bool ELFObjectWriter::shouldRelocateWithSymbol(const MCAssembler &Asm, 0
1300 const MCSymbolRefExpr *RefA, ----
1301 const MCSymbolELF *Sym, ----
1302 uint64_t C, ----
1303 unsigned Type) const { ----
1304 // A PCRel relocation to an absolute value has no symbol (or section). We ----
1305 // represent that with a relocation to a null section. ----
1306 if (!RefA) 0
1307 return false; 0
1308 ----
1309 MCSymbolRefExpr::VariantKind Kind = RefA->getKind(); 0
1310 switch (Kind) { 0
1311 default: 0
1312 break; 0
1313 // The .odp creation emits a relocation against the symbol ".TOC." which ----
1314 // create a R_PPC64_TOC relocation. However the relocation symbol name ----
1315 // in final object creation should be NULL, since the symbol does not ----
1316 // really exist, it is just the reference to TOC base for the current ----
1317 // object file. Since the symbol is undefined, returning false results ----
1318 // in a relocation with a null section which is the desired result. ----
1319 case MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_PPC_TOCBASE: 0
1320 return false; 0
1321 ----
1322 // These VariantKind cause the relocation to refer to something other than ----
1323 // the symbol itself, like a linker generated table. Since the address of ----
1324 // symbol is not relevant, we cannot replace the symbol with the ----
1325 // section and patch the difference in the addend. ----
1326 case MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_GOT: 0
1327 case MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_PLT: ----
1328 case MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_GOTPCREL: ----
1329 case MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_GOTPCREL_NORELAX: ----
1330 case MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_PPC_GOT_LO: ----
1331 case MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_PPC_GOT_HI: ----
1332 case MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_PPC_GOT_HA: ----
1333 return true; 0
1334 } ----
1335 ----
1336 // An undefined symbol is not in any section, so the relocation has to point ----
1337 // to the symbol itself. ----
1338 assert(Sym && "Expected a symbol"); 0
1339 if (Sym->isUndefined()) 0
1340 return true; 0
1341 ----
1342 // For memory-tagged symbols, ensure that the relocation uses the symbol. For ----
1343 // tagged symbols, we emit an empty relocation (R_AARCH64_NONE) in a special ----
1344 // section (SHT_AARCH64_MEMTAG_GLOBALS_STATIC) to indicate to the linker that ----
1345 // this global needs to be tagged. In addition, the linker needs to know ----
1346 // whether to emit a special addend when relocating `end` symbols, and this ----
1347 // can only be determined by the attributes of the symbol itself. ----
1348 if (Sym->isMemtag()) 0
1349 return true; 0
1350 ----
1351 unsigned Binding = Sym->getBinding(); 0
1352 switch(Binding) { 0
1353 default: 0
1354 llvm_unreachable("Invalid Binding"); 0
1355 case ELF::STB_LOCAL: 0
1356 break; 0
1357 case ELF::STB_WEAK: 0
1358 // If the symbol is weak, it might be overridden by a symbol in another ----
1359 // file. The relocation has to point to the symbol so that the linker ----
1360 // can update it. ----
1361 return true; 0
1362 case ELF::STB_GLOBAL: 0
1363 case ELF::STB_GNU_UNIQUE: ----
1364 // Global ELF symbols can be preempted by the dynamic linker. The relocation ----
1365 // has to point to the symbol for a reason analogous to the STB_WEAK case. ----
1366 return true; 0
1367 } ----
1368 ----
1369 // Keep symbol type for a local ifunc because it may result in an IRELATIVE ----
1370 // reloc that the dynamic loader will use to resolve the address at startup ----
1371 // time. ----
1372 if (Sym->getType() == ELF::STT_GNU_IFUNC) 0
1373 return true; 0
1374 ----
1375 // If a relocation points to a mergeable section, we have to be careful. ----
1376 // If the offset is zero, a relocation with the section will encode the ----
1377 // same information. With a non-zero offset, the situation is different. ----
1378 // For example, a relocation can point 42 bytes past the end of a string. ----
1379 // If we change such a relocation to use the section, the linker would think ----
1380 // that it pointed to another string and subtracting 42 at runtime will ----
1381 // produce the wrong value. ----
1382 if (Sym->isInSection()) { 0
1383 auto &Sec = cast(Sym->getSection()); 0
1384 unsigned Flags = Sec.getFlags(); 0
1385 if (Flags & ELF::SHF_MERGE) { 0
1386 if (C != 0) 0
1387 return true; 0
1388 ----
1389 // gold<2.34 incorrectly ignored the addend for R_386_GOTOFF (9) ----
1390 // (http://sourceware.org/PR16794). ----
1391 if (TargetObjectWriter->getEMachine() == ELF::EM_386 && 0
1392 Type == ELF::R_386_GOTOFF) ----
1393 return true; 0
1394 ----
1395 // ld.lld handles R_MIPS_HI16/R_MIPS_LO16 separately, not as a whole, so ----
1396 // it doesn't know that an R_MIPS_HI16 with implicit addend 1 and an ----
1397 // R_MIPS_LO16 with implicit addend -32768 represents 32768, which is in ----
1398 // range of a MergeInputSection. We could introduce a new RelExpr member ----
1399 // (like R_RISCV_PC_INDIRECT for R_RISCV_PCREL_HI20 / R_RISCV_PCREL_LO12) ----
1400 // but the complexity is unnecessary given that GNU as keeps the original ----
1401 // symbol for this case as well. ----
1402 if (TargetObjectWriter->getEMachine() == ELF::EM_MIPS && 0
1403 !hasRelocationAddend()) 0
1404 return true; 0
1405 } ----
1406 ----
1407 // Most TLS relocations use a got, so they need the symbol. Even those that ----
1408 // are just an offset (@tpoff), require a symbol in gold versions before ----
1409 // 5efeedf61e4fe720fd3e9a08e6c91c10abb66d42 (2014-09-26) which fixed ----
1410 // http://sourceware.org/PR16773. ----
1411 if (Flags & ELF::SHF_TLS) 0
1412 return true; 0
1413 } ----
1414 ----
1415 // If the symbol is a thumb function the final relocation must set the lowest ----
1416 // bit. With a symbol that is done by just having the symbol have that bit ----
1417 // set, so we would lose the bit if we relocated with the section. ----
1418 // FIXME: We could use the section but add the bit to the relocation value. ----
1419 if (Asm.isThumbFunc(Sym)) 0
1420 return true; 0
1421 ----
1422 if (TargetObjectWriter->needsRelocateWithSymbol(*Sym, Type)) 0
1423 return true; 0
1424 return false; 0
1425 } ----

1427 void ELFObjectWriter::recordRelocation(MCAssembler &Asm, 0
1428 const MCAsmLayout &Layout, ----
1429 const MCFragment *Fragment, ----
1430 const MCFixup &Fixup, MCValue Target, ----
1431 uint64_t &FixedValue) { ----
1432 MCAsmBackend &Backend = Asm.getBackend(); 0
1433 bool IsPCRel = Backend.getFixupKindInfo(Fixup.getKind()).Flags & 0
1434 MCFixupKindInfo::FKF_IsPCRel; 0
1435 const MCSectionELF &FixupSection = cast(*Fragment->getParent()); 0
1436 uint64_t C = Target.getConstant(); 0
1437 uint64_t FixupOffset = Layout.getFragmentOffset(Fragment) + Fixup.getOffset(); 0
1438 MCContext &Ctx = Asm.getContext(); 0
1439 ----
1440 if (const MCSymbolRefExpr *RefB = Target.getSymB()) { 0
1441 const auto &SymB = cast(RefB->getSymbol()); 0
1442 if (SymB.isUndefined()) { 0
1443 Ctx.reportError(Fixup.getLoc(), 0
1444 Twine("symbol '") + SymB.getName() + 0
1445 "' can not be undefined in a subtraction expression"); 0
1446 return; 0
1447 } ----
1448 ----
1449 assert(!SymB.isAbsolute() && "Should have been folded"); 0
1450 const MCSection &SecB = SymB.getSection(); 0
1451 if (&SecB != &FixupSection) { 0
1452 Ctx.reportError(Fixup.getLoc(), 0
1453 "Cannot represent a difference across sections"); ----
1454 return; 0
1455 } ----
1456 ----
1457 assert(!IsPCRel && "should have been folded"); 0
1458 IsPCRel = true; 0
1459 C += FixupOffset - Layout.getSymbolOffset(SymB); 0
1460 } ----
1461 ----
1462 // We either rejected the fixup or folded B into C at this point. ----
1463 const MCSymbolRefExpr *RefA = Target.getSymA(); 0
1464 const auto *SymA = RefA ? cast(&RefA->getSymbol()) : nullptr; 0
1465 ----
1466 bool ViaWeakRef = false; 0
1467 if (SymA && SymA->isVariable()) { 0
1468 const MCExpr *Expr = SymA->getVariableValue(); 0
1469 if (const auto *Inner = dyn_cast(Expr)) { 0
1470 if (Inner->getKind() == MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_WEAKREF) { 0
1471 SymA = cast(&Inner->getSymbol()); 0
1472 ViaWeakRef = true; 0
1473 } ----
1474 } ----
1475 } ----
1476 ----
1477 const MCSectionELF *SecA = (SymA && SymA->isInSection()) 0
1478 ? cast(&SymA->getSection()) 0
1479 : nullptr; 0
1480 if (!checkRelocation(Ctx, Fixup.getLoc(), &FixupSection, SecA)) 0
1481 return; 0
1482 ----
1483 unsigned Type = TargetObjectWriter->getRelocType(Ctx, Target, Fixup, IsPCRel); 0
1484 const auto *Parent = cast(Fragment->getParent()); 0
1485 // Emiting relocation with sybmol for CG Profile to help with --cg-profile. ----
1486 bool RelocateWithSymbol = ----
1487 shouldRelocateWithSymbol(Asm, RefA, SymA, C, Type) || 0
1488 (Parent->getType() == ELF::SHT_LLVM_CALL_GRAPH_PROFILE); 0
1489 uint64_t Addend = 0; 0
1490 ----
1491 FixedValue = !RelocateWithSymbol && SymA && !SymA->isUndefined() 0
1492 ? C + Layout.getSymbolOffset(*SymA) 0
1493 : C; ----
1494 if (hasRelocationAddend()) { 0
1495 Addend = FixedValue; 0
1496 FixedValue = 0; 0
1497 } ----
1498 ----
1499 if (!RelocateWithSymbol) { 0
1500 const auto *SectionSymbol = ----
1501 SecA ? cast(SecA->getBeginSymbol()) : nullptr; 0
1502 if (SectionSymbol) 0
1503 SectionSymbol->setUsedInReloc(); 0
1504 ELFRelocationEntry Rec(FixupOffset, SectionSymbol, Type, Addend, SymA, C); 0
1505 Relocations[&FixupSection].push_back(Rec); 0
1506 return; 0
1507 } ----
1508 ----
1509 const MCSymbolELF *RenamedSymA = SymA; 0
1510 if (SymA) { 0
1511 if (const MCSymbolELF *R = Renames.lookup(SymA)) 0
1512 RenamedSymA = R; 0
1513 ----
1514 if (ViaWeakRef) 0
1515 RenamedSymA->setIsWeakrefUsedInReloc(); 0
1516 else ----
1517 RenamedSymA->setUsedInReloc(); 0
1518 } ----
1519 ELFRelocationEntry Rec(FixupOffset, RenamedSymA, Type, Addend, SymA, C); 0
1520 Relocations[&FixupSection].push_back(Rec); 0
1521 } ----

1534 InSet, IsPCRel); 0

397 // ELF Header 397 // ELF Header
398 // ---------- 398 // ----------
399 // 399 //
400 // Note 400 // Note
401 // ---- 401 // ----
402 // emitWord method behaves differently for ELF32 and ELF64, writing 402 // emitWord method behaves differently for ELF32 and ELF64, writing
403 // 4 bytes in the former and 8 in the latter. 403 // 4 bytes in the former and 8 in the latter.
404 404
405 W.OS << ELF::ElfMagic; // e_ident[EI_MAG0] to e_ident[EI_MAG3] 405 W.OS << ELF::ElfMagic; // e_ident[EI_MAG0] to e_ident[EI_MAG3]

408 408
409 // e_ident[EI_DATA] 409 // e_ident[EI_DATA]
410 W.OS << char(W.Endian == support::little ? ELF::ELFDATA2LSB 410 W.OS << char(W.Endian == support::little ? ELF::ELFDATA2LSB
411 : ELF::ELFDATA2MSB); 411 : ELF::ELFDATA2MSB);
412 412

414 // e_ident[EI_OSABI] 414 // e_ident[EI_OSABI]
415 uint8_t OSABI = OWriter.TargetObjectWriter->getOSABI(); 415 uint8_t OSABI = OWriter.TargetObjectWriter->getOSABI();
416 W.OS << char(OSABI == ELF::ELFOSABI_NONE && OWriter.seenGnuAbi() 416 W.OS << char(OSABI == ELF::ELFOSABI_NONE && OWriter.seenGnuAbi()
417 ? int(ELF::ELFOSABI_GNU) 417 ? int(ELF::ELFOSABI_GNU)
418 : OSABI); 418 : OSABI);

420 W.OS << char(OWriter.TargetObjectWriter->getABIVersion()); 420 W.OS << char(OWriter.TargetObjectWriter->getABIVersion());

425 425

427 427
428 W.write(ELF::EV_CURRENT); // e_version 428 W.write(ELF::EV_CURRENT); // e_version
429 WriteWord(0); // e_entry, no entry point in .o file 429 WriteWord(0); // e_entry, no entry point in .o file
430 WriteWord(0); // e_phoff, no program header for .o 430 WriteWord(0); // e_phoff, no program header for .o
431 WriteWord(0); // e_shoff = sec hdr table off in bytes 431 WriteWord(0); // e_shoff = sec hdr table off in bytes
432 432
433 // e_flags = whatever the target wants 433 // e_flags = whatever the target wants
434 W.write(Asm.getELFHeaderEFlags()); 434 W.write(Asm.getELFHeaderEFlags());
435 435
436 // e_ehsize = ELF header size 436 // e_ehsize = ELF header size
437 W.write(is64Bit() ? sizeof(ELF::Elf64_Ehdr) 437 W.write(is64Bit() ? sizeof(ELF::Elf64_Ehdr)
438 : sizeof(ELF::Elf32_Ehdr)); 438 : sizeof(ELF::Elf32_Ehdr));
439 439
440 W.write(0); // e_phentsize = prog header entry size 440 W.write(0); // e_phentsize = prog header entry size
441 W.write(0); // e_phnum = # prog header entries = 0 441 W.write(0); // e_phnum = # prog header entries = 0

447 // e_shnum = # of section header ents 447 // e_shnum = # of section header ents

470 static uint8_t mergeTypeForSet(uint8_t origType, uint8_t newType) { 470 static uint8_t mergeTypeForSet(uint8_t origType, uint8_t newType) {
471 uint8_t Type = newType; 471 uint8_t Type = newType;
472 472
473 // Propagation rules: 473 // Propagation rules:
474 // IFUNC > FUNC > OBJECT > NOTYPE 474 // IFUNC > FUNC > OBJECT > NOTYPE
475 // TLS_OBJECT > OBJECT > NOTYPE 475 // TLS_OBJECT > OBJECT > NOTYPE
476 // 476 //
477 // dont let the new type degrade the old type 477 // dont let the new type degrade the old type
478 switch (origType) { 478 switch (origType) {
479 default: 479 default:
480 break; 480 break;
481 case ELF::STT_GNU_IFUNC: 481 case ELF::STT_GNU_IFUNC:
482 if (Type == ELF::STT_FUNC || Type == ELF::STT_OBJECT || 482 if (Type == ELF::STT_FUNC || Type == ELF::STT_OBJECT ||
483 Type == ELF::STT_NOTYPE || Type == ELF::STT_TLS) 483 Type == ELF::STT_NOTYPE || Type == ELF::STT_TLS)
484 Type = ELF::STT_GNU_IFUNC; 484 Type = ELF::STT_GNU_IFUNC;
485 break; 485 break;
486 case ELF::STT_FUNC: 486 case ELF::STT_FUNC:
487 if (Type == ELF::STT_OBJECT || Type == ELF::STT_NOTYPE || 487 if (Type == ELF::STT_OBJECT || Type == ELF::STT_NOTYPE ||
488 Type == ELF::STT_TLS) 488 Type == ELF::STT_TLS)
489 Type = ELF::STT_FUNC; 489 Type = ELF::STT_FUNC;
490 break; 490 break;
491 case ELF::STT_OBJECT: 491 case ELF::STT_OBJECT:
492 if (Type == ELF::STT_NOTYPE) 492 if (Type == ELF::STT_NOTYPE)
493 Type = ELF::STT_OBJECT; 493 Type = ELF::STT_OBJECT;
494 break; 494 break;
495 case ELF::STT_TLS: 495 case ELF::STT_TLS:
496 if (Type == ELF::STT_OBJECT || Type == ELF::STT_NOTYPE || 496 if (Type == ELF::STT_OBJECT || Type == ELF::STT_NOTYPE ||
497 Type == ELF::STT_GNU_IFUNC || Type == ELF::STT_FUNC) 497 Type == ELF::STT_GNU_IFUNC || Type == ELF::STT_FUNC)
498 Type = ELF::STT_TLS; 498 Type = ELF::STT_TLS;

500 } 500 }

503 } 503 }
